// The Ledger, chapter 2 of 4, part one: CLAIM JUMPERS. The Magpies come to
// take the box: a pair of light corvettes burn in from the eastern lane
// while the Dray Mule - the company hauler carrying the find - must
// survive. Reworked by the difficulty spike (tasks/20260717-111808/SPIKE.md
// F1/F2/F3/F4/F6): light turrets on the wave-one mooks, spawns pushed out
// to ~600u so an approach phase exists, both attackers on ONE bearing (no
// bracketing crossfire), an invulnerable rock field between their lane and
// the Mule (real cover - the AI line-of-fire gate holds fire when a rock
// blocks the shot), and the Mule stationed off the threat axis in the
// rocks' lee. Chapter two is act-split for retry: this file is wave one
// only; dying here retries wave one, and breaking the wave checkpoints
// into ledger_ch2b (The Heavies).
//
// Acts: 1 = the fight, 2 = wave broken (victory beat). Kill gates use
// `> N-1`, never `== N` (count-gate lesson); the Defeat handlers gate
// act < 2 so a post-victory loss cannot overwrite the win.
[
    Scenario((
        id: "ledger_ch2_claim_jumpers",
        name: "The Ledger 2: Claim Jumpers",
        description: "The Magpies want the box. Break their first wave and keep them off the Dray Mule. Chapter two of The Ledger, wave one.",
        cubemap: "dep://base/textures/cubemap_alt.png",
        thumbnail: Some("dep://base/textures/asteroid.png"),
        hidden: true,
        events: [
