                    // Hard cover: an invulnerable rock arc between the
                    // eastern approach lane and the Mule's station. Nominal
                    // radii are small on purpose - asteroid bodies run
                    // 3.5x-6x nominal (ASTEROID_GEOMETRIC_FACTOR_MIN/MAX),
                    // so a nominal 4 is a ~15-24u boulder. Centers are
                    // spaced so worst-case 6x bodies overlap nothing.
